And I also point out-- now,
obviously the one of them

00:29:06.350 --> 00:29:07.967
looking at product
labels, that one--

00:29:07.967 --> 00:29:09.050
we're not quite there yet.

00:29:09.050 --> 00:29:10.910
But we're working toward that.

00:29:10.910 --> 00:29:13.610
And just educating
them to be consumers

00:29:13.610 --> 00:29:16.220
that think about these things.

00:29:16.220 --> 00:29:17.870
Hopefully some of it
is going to stick.

00:29:17.870 --> 00:29:19.250
And it's certainly
easier if I can just

00:29:19.250 --> 00:29:21.990
tell them when they're shopping
look for this logo on products.

00:29:21.990 --> 00:29:23.531
And in fact, for
many years, they're,

00:29:23.531 --> 00:29:25.350
Daddy, your logo's
on this product.

00:29:25.350 --> 00:29:27.410
In fact, one of my
favorite examples

00:29:27.410 --> 00:29:29.210
is the Subway chain
of restaurants.

00:29:29.210 --> 00:29:31.910
In all 25,000 Subways
in North America

00:29:31.910 --> 00:29:34.760
has a Green Seal certified
hand soap in their restrooms

00:29:34.760 --> 00:29:36.830
and behind the sink for
the sandwich artists

00:29:36.830 --> 00:29:37.970
to wash their hands.

00:29:37.970 --> 00:29:39.560
So we come from
a sporting event,

00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:42.559
we hit Subway to get a
healthier sandwich for dinner,

00:29:42.559 --> 00:29:44.850
and the kids all go in the
bathroom to wash their hands

00:29:44.850 --> 00:29:47.000
and they see the Green
Seal on the little window

00:29:47.000 --> 00:29:47.930
in the soap dispenser.

00:29:47.930 --> 00:29:49.627
And it warms my heart.

00:29:49.627 --> 00:29:51.710
So finding that once you
get them trained to start

00:29:51.710 --> 00:29:53.494
looking for it, it is possible.

00:29:53.494 --> 00:29:55.910
And, of course, for my daughter,
for every serious picture

00:29:55.910 --> 00:29:58.285
we take she has to take one
that's a not serious picture.

00:29:58.285 --> 00:30:03.250
So that's her go to
not serious face.

